  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.8-unstable`\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 version 21H1\r\nCommit hash : dfeb2f7e8001aef1005a8d5e1605bae1de0b4f12\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen running ``geth show-deprecated-flags``, the deprecated flags listed shouldn't be one hard to pronounce run-on sentence; they should have something like a ``:`` directly before the description of the command for easier readability.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nWhen running ``geth show-deprecated-flags``, the flags are spit out with no commas or breaks between them.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun ``geth show-deprecated-flags``.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nC:\\Users\\zachinquarantine>geth show-deprecated-flags\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nThe following flags are deprecated and will be removed in the future!\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n--miner.gastarget value Target gas floor for mined blocks (deprecated) (default: 0)\r\n--nousb Disables monitoring for and managing USB hardware wallets (deprecated)\r\n````\r\n\r\nAs shown above, right after ``--miner.gastarget value`` and after ``--nousb``, there is no break before the description of the flag.\r\nWhat it could say instead is:\r\n````\r\nC:\\Users\\zachinquarantine>geth show-deprecated-flags\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nThe following flags are deprecated and will be removed in the future!\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n--miner.gastarget value: Target gas floor for mined blocks (deprecated) (default: 0)\r\n--nousb: Disables monitoring for and managing USB hardware wallets (deprecated)\r\n````",
